law.text:
For purposes of this Part I of this subtitle, an electronic signature shall have the same effect as a manual signature if the electronic signature:
Uses an algorithm approved by the National Institute of Standards and Technology;
Is unique to the individual using it;
Is capable of verification;
Is under the sole control of the individual using it;
Is linked to data in such a manner that if the data are changed, the electronic signature is invalidated;
Persists with the document and not by association in separate files; and
Is bound to a digital certificate.
